_pdbx_entry_details.entry_id                 229L 
_pdbx_entry_details.compound_details         
;STRUCTURE OF A T4 LYSOZYME MUTANT WITH A POLAR CREVICE,
CREATED BY TRUNCATING ARG 95 TO ALA.  ARG 95 PARTICIPATES
IN A SALT BRIDGE WITH ASP 92 AND THE MUTANT IS VERY
DESTABILIZED (~5 KCAL/MOL) (ANDERSON,MCINTOSH,DAHLQUIST IN
"NMR OF PROTEINS", (M.CLORE,A.GRONENBORN, EDS.,
MACMILLAN)).  THE MUTANT IS STABILIZED TO THERMAL
DENATURATION BY 0-50 MM GUANIDIUM.  ISOMORPHOUS CRYSTALS
ONLY GROW IN THE PRESENCE OF GUANIDINIUM.  THE LIGAND
BINDS AT THE ARG 95 SIDE CHAIN SITE AND APPARENTLY
RECONSTITUTES THE SALT BRIDGE AND A NEARBY CRYSTAL CONTACT.
;
